Change2):-In Update Module Added ADD/REPLACE option for “Remote Subnet”
=========================================================================
Step-by-step (what we did so far)

1) Added ADD/REPLACE option for “Remote Subnet” in the Update modal
   - In renderUpdateFields(), when choice "3" is selected:
     a) Added a “Remote Subnet Action” dropdown (add / replace)
     b) Added NEW remote subnet inputs: new_remote_ip, new_remote_mask
     c) If “replace” is selected, show OLD subnet inputs: old_remote_ip, old_remote_mask

2) Fixed instant show/hide for OLD subnet fields
   - After setting sel.onchange, we called:
     sel.onchange();
     So if “replace” is already selected, the old fields appear immediately.

3) Fixed submitUpdate() payload for Remote Subnet
   - In submitUpdate(), for choice "3":
     payload.remote_action
     payload.new_remote_ip + payload.new_remote_mask
     If remote_action === "replace":
       payload.old_remote_ip + payload.old_remote_mask

4) Removed wrong UI code from submitUpdate()
   - Earlier, UI code (container.innerHTML / onchange) accidentally went into submitUpdate().
   - We removed it and kept UI rendering only inside renderUpdateFields().

5) Added/ensured closeModal() exists
   - So Cancel works and the modal closes after success.
   - Also resets updateChoice and clears updateDynamicFields.

6) Added GUI warning + Yes/No confirmation for REPLACE
   - Before calling fetch() for the update request:
     show confirm() popup
     If user clicks No -> cancel and return
     If user clicks Yes -> set payload.user_confirmed = true

7) Enforced confirmation in backend for REPLACE (safety)
   - In update.py, before applying the replace:
     If payload.user_confirmed is not true -> cancel and return

8) Started making warning text consistent (same message)
   - Standard warning text we decided:
     "⚠️ WARNING: VPN traffic may be impacted if remote side is not updated. Do you want to proceed?"
   - This can be used in both frontend confirm and backend prints.

9) Added requirement for ADD to show warning BEFORE doing the change
   - Add the same confirm() popup for remote_action === "add" before fetch().
   - (Optional) also enforce it on backend using a flag (extra safety).

10) Added/used “AFTER show run access-list” output (verification)
   - After adding a subnet, print the ACL again so you can confirm the new subnet appears.